Single `IN` query. 1 round-trip for 3 or 47 SKUs. No pool pressure, no concurrency tuning.

```js
async function checkInventory(skus) {
  const rows = await db.query(
    'SELECT sku, stock FROM inventory WHERE sku = ANY($1)',
    [skus]
  );
  const map = new Map(rows.map(r => [r.sku, r.stock]));
  return skus.map(s => ({ sku: s, stock: map.get(s) ?? 0 }));
}
```

Why win:
- 3 SKUs: 1 query vs 3 parallel → faster common case
- 47 SKUs: 1 query vs 47 parallel → no pool spike
- Flat latency curve, predictable

Fallback if schema blocks `IN`: `p-limit(5)` caps concurrency, worst case 47/5 ≈ 10 serial batches.

